    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="How does automation work in Holosim?" class="article-title">
          How does automation work in Holosim?
          
        </h1>

        <div class="article-author">
          
          <div class="article-meta">
            

            <div class="meta-group">
              
                <span class="meta-data"><time datetime="2025-12-08T18:24:06Z" title="2025-12-08T18:24:06Z" data-datetime="relative">December 08, 2025 18:24</time></span>
                <span class="meta-data">Updated</span>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        
          <div class="article-subscribe"><div data-helper="subscribe" data-json="{&quot;item&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/hc/en-us/articles/47031333660563-How-does-automation-work-in-Holosim/subscription.json&quot;,&quot;follow_label&quot;:&quot;Follow&quot;,&quot;unfollow_label&quot;:&quot;Unfollow&quot;,&quot;following_label&quot;:&quot;Following&quot;,&quot;can_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;is_subscribed&quot;:false}"></div></div>
        
      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><p>Automation in Holosim allows your fleets to run <strong>routes</strong> automatically, repeating tasks like mining, transporting, or patrolling without needing constant manual input.</p><h3 id="h_01KBG7FET5BTKJ93M7R9KABCSW">How to enable automation:</h3><ol><li><p><strong>Open “My Fleets”: </strong>click the <strong>My Fleets</strong> tab to see your fleets.</p></li><li><p><strong>Select a fleet: </strong>choose the fleet you want to automate.</p></li><li><p><strong>Click the automation icon: </strong>look for the symbol with a curved arrow and gear&nbsp;</p><p><img class="hs-image-align-none" style="height: auto;" src="https://20489070.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/20489070/image-png-Sep-25-2025-05-17-09-4817-PM.png" width="583" height="59"></p></li><li><p><strong>Enable route: </strong>click <strong>“Enable Route.”</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Choose an action: </strong>select one of the available automation tasks:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Mining: </strong>automatically mine resources.</p></li><li><p><strong>Transport: </strong>move goods between bases.</p></li><li><p><strong>Patrol: </strong>keep your fleet active in specific areas.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Set the details: </strong>depending on the action, you may need to choose:</p><ul><li><p>Which base or resource to mine.</p></li><li><p>The origin and destination for transport.</p></li><li><p>The patrol sector.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Assign the automation: </strong>once configured, confirm to activate.</p></li></ol><h3 id="h_01KBG7FET5J8WBDESK3GF1A0YE">How to stop automation:</h3><ul><li><p>Open the same fleet, click the automation icon again, and <strong>disable the route.</strong> This stops the automated task immediately.</p></li></ul><p>Automation helps you save time and keep multiple fleets working in the background, but make sure you have enough crew, food, fuel, and resources to sustain the tasks.</p></div>

          

          
        </div>
      </section>

